The paper deals with the application of deep learning models for skin lesion segmentation and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed model involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and mutual bootstrapping, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed model using performance metrics, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
